title: Grateful Dead Live at Shrine Auditorium on 1978-01-11
description:
Set 1

Minglewood Blues, Dire Wolf, Looks Like Rain, They Love Each Other, Big River-> El Paso, Brown Eyed Women, Let It Grow

Set 2

Samson & Delilah, Sunrise, Terrapin Station-> Playin' In The Band-> Saint Stephen-> Not Fade Away-> Playin' In The Band, E: Passenger

reviews.review_text:
The only game in town.. This is a top notch show.
There are many high intensity jams
flirting with meltdowns  
especially Jerry!
Let it grow thru PITB reprise-Wow.
Passenger is a rockin' encore.

Get Shone The Light Every once in a while, I discover a great show that, for whatever reason, I never really listened to back in the day. It doesn’t happen often, but when it does, it still genuinely excites - even after all these years. Like finding a diamond sitting in plain sight and wondering how the hell I missed it all this time. That happened tonight when I spun the wayback wheel and landed on this date and recording. I started with the set 1 closing Let It Grow and, bloody hell, it blew my socks clean off.  Must’ve been something in the ether that night (or possibly actual ether, it was 1978 after all). Jerry ferociously attacks the jam (starting about 4:20) and unleashes wave after wave of rapid fire searing lines and thunderous peaks. Yeah, whoa. The entire 2d set is a rager, starting with a booming Samson and ending with a powerhouse Playing reprise and Passenger encore. Be sure to check out the spectacular St. Stephen and surrounding jams, which feel like a mini “best of ‘77” review. O’h it’s a keeper alright. Run don’t walk to this one.
